Wash and dry produce.

Trim @scallions{2}; cut scallion whites into 1-inch pieces and thinly slice
scallion greens. Trim root end from @baby lettuce{1}; separate leaves.

In a small #microwave-safe bowl{}, mix @shredded carrots{4%oz}, 
@rice wine vinegar{5%tsp}, @water{1%tsp}, @sugar{1%tsp}, a big pinch of @salt{},
and @pepper{} (for 4, use a medium bowl, 2 tsp water, and 2 tsp sugar). Cover
with #plastic wrap{}; microwave for ~{30%seconds}. Set aside to pickle,
stirring occasionally.

Pat @ranch steak{10%oz} dry; thinly slice crosswise into strips. Season all
over with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Drizzle @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a hot #large pan{}. Add steak and scallion
whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until scallions are charred and steak
is cooked to desired doneness, ~{3-6%minutes}.

In the last minute of cooking, stir in half the @bulgogi sauce{4%oz} (all
for 4). Cook until slightly thickened.

Meanwhile, massage @microwavable rice{1} in package to break up grains;
partially open package. Microwave until warmed through, ~{90%seconds}.

> Microwave times may vary. Be careful when handling and opening the pouch.

In a second small #bowl{}, mix @sweet Thai chili sauce{1%oz} and 
@mayonnaise{2%tbsp}. Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if desired.

Fan lettuce leaves out on a #plate{} or #cutting board{}. Place rice, steak,
pickled carrots (draining first), and creamy chili sauce in separate
#serving bowls{}. Sprinkle steak with @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} and garnish rice
with scallion greens. Serve family style.

> Steak is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.